Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Very clear sky.  Thundershowers previous evening.  Light WNW winds.
Partly cloudy- haze- light sun- eastward wind at 5 mph- air 70 degrees.  Lake level: At spillway-even
Clear- hot- sunny- light NW wind- much boating over holiday weekend in shallows.
Cloudy- light rain- no wind- 1/2" accumulated rain.  Lake level: Rising
Sunny- light breeze- water temperature at pier 76 degrees.
Sunny day- light breeze- water temperature 78 degrees.
Breezy- clear day- boating on lake reduced.
Slight haze.  Winds SE @ 10 mph.  High winds and waves several days earlier.  Water level: very low.
Test followed several days of rain and wind- marl accumulating on sand beach.  Lake level: Rising
Tests for balance of 88 and 89 less frequent.
Clear sky- winds 5-10 mph from SE.  Outdoor in Wisconsin-it doesn't get any better than this!!  Lake Level:  dropping lake level at dam
Skim ice previous night.  Heavy winds previous week.  Water looks cloudy/turbid.  Winds in AM light from north-northwest.  Sky is mostly clear.
Clear- winds southwest-s light and variable.  No ice on lake.
Ice off approx. one week ago.  Some pack ice in north end.  SE winds 10 mph.  Clear sky.  Air temp. 10 degrees C.
Oxygen monitoring showed Dissolved Oxygen. near saturation.  Surface temperature is 77 degrees- O2 is 9.1 parts per million.
First clear day following six rainy stormy days.  Water temperature 62 degrees.
Bright day- light breeze and chop water temperature is 80 degrees from shore 76 degrees.
Bright day- light chop- SW wind- water temperature is 80 degrees at the pier.
Wind NE 4-8 mph. Sky is clear.
Partly cloudy- calm- 72 degree water temperature.
Surface water temperature = 23.8 degrees Celsius.  Dissolved oxygen = 8.2 parts per million by YSI meter. NW winds 15-30 mph.  Air temperature is 15 degrees Celsius.
Bright and clear- winds light from northwest.  Surface water temperature @ 62 degrees F.  Water level: very low.
Light NW wind- clear- test followed several windy days.  Water level: very low.
Clear sky- air temperature at 60 degrees F- wind SW at 5-10 mph.  "Indian summer"
Three inches of new clear ice.  Ice on 11/22-23.  Clear sky.  Lake level being dropped
Partly cloudy- light winds from se.  Air temperature 75 degrees F.  3.61" of rain from 7/2-7/31.
Clear sky- winds NW at 5 mph.  Air temp 80 degrees F.  2.83" of rain from 8/1-8/31.
Lake being lowered for winter.  Partly sunny- west wind at 15-20 mph.  4.35" of rain from 9/1-9/22.  The air temperature is 54 degrees F.
The lake level is dropping.  Winds west at 15-20 mph- and a clear sky.  3.3" of rain from 9/22-10/27.
Clear sky- winds 10 mph northeast- 55 degrees F air temp.
Clear sky- winds 5-10 northwest- air temp 70 degrees F.
Clear sky- winds SE 10-12 mph- air temp 80 degrees temp- water temp (surface) is 76 degrees F.
Partly cloudy- wind w/d- air 70 degrees.
Series of windy days- water temperature near shore is 78 degrees.
Partly cloudy skies- southeast winds at 5 mph- and the air temperature is 72 degrees F.
Light SE wind- bright sunny day.
Partly cloudy- the air temperature is 76 degrees F- northwest winds at 5-10 mph- light rain several hours prior to sampling.
10-12 mph SW wind- very warm weather.
Bright sunny day- light S wind.
Winds WNW at 10-15 mph- the air temperature is 40 degrees F- there were strong northwest wins the previous day.
Northwest wind at 10-15 mph- the air temperature is 38 degrees F- and it is sunny and cold.
SE winds 10-12 mph.  Air temp 65 degrees F.  Sunny
WNW winds 15-25 mph.- mostly sunny- 70 degrees F.
Clear- quiet day.  Following heavy rains.
Partly cloudy- winds NW 10 mph.- 74 degrees F air- .5" rain previous night- light boating activity.
.5" rain last night- mostly cloudy- NW winds 15-20 mph.
Breezy- clear- very little boat activity for 2-3 weeks.
Sunny- wind NE 5-10- air 60 degrees F.
Overcast- winds SW 5 mph- air temp=32 degrees F.
Winds NNW @ 10-15 mph- clear sky- air temp. 40-45 degrees.  Water level: 2" over spillway
Partly cloudy- NW winds 15-20 mph- air temp 50.
Clear sky- east-southeast winds 5 mph- air temp 70.
Turbid lake- SE wind 12-15 mph- air temp 75- clear sky.
Partly sunny- 70-75- water brown/green- very turbid.
High SE winds 15-25 mph thus turbid waters- mostly cloudy- rain earlier in day.
SE wind 5 mph- partly cloudy- air temp 80.
Partly cloudy- air temp 65- N winds @ 5 mph.
Wind NW 5-10 mph- clear- air temp is 50 degrees.
Partly cloudy- air temp is 65 degrees- windy SW @ 5 mph.
Winds NE 5-10 mph- sunny- air temp is 60 degrees.
Winds SE 20-25 mph- rough water- marl being suspended- water temp. 60 degrees- sunny - 70 degrees.
Windy SE 5-10- sunny- air temp. 80 degrees- marl suspended.
Winds SE 15 mph- sunny- air temp is 75 degrees- suspended marl.
Wind SW 15-20 mph.  Sunny lake very turbid- appears to be suspended.
Partly cloudy- winds east-southeast @ 5-10 mph- no boat traffic- some rain previous day- suspended marl.
Public perception due to marl.  Winds NE 15 mph- clear sky- air temp. 65 degrees F- suspended marl.
Public perception due to marl.  Winds east-southeast 10-12 mph- clear sky- air temp. 72 degrees F- heavy boat traffic.
Sunny- winds 15+ mph west- air temp. 80 degrees +.
Clear sky- winds are NW 5 mph- minimal boating activity- rain and storm the previous evening.
Winds SW 10-15 mph- sunny- some marl suspended.
Winds SE 25-30 mph- sunny' air temp. 75 degrees F- marl suspended.
Winds NE 10-12 mph- sunny' air temp. 65 degrees F.  High winds and waves suspended marl on 8/6 + 8/7 - less on 8/8.
Public perception due to marl levels.  Winds NW 10-15 mph- sunny.
Marl problems- winds light from northwest.  Sunny + calm.  Little boat traffic.
Winds ESE less than 5 mph- calm- sunny- air temp. 65 degrees F.
East winds 5 mph- partly sunny- water=70 degrees F- air=68 degrees F- rain earlier.
Bright and sunny- winds are SE @ 10 mph- light chop- no boat traffic- air temp is 65 degrees.
Winds SE 15-20 mph- sunny' air temp. 65 degrees F.
Turbidity persists.  Sunny.  West winds at 10-15 mph.
Clear + sunny- 50 degrees F- winds SE 10 mph.  First secchi reading of '95.
Public perception due to turbidity.  Winds east-southeast 15 mph- waves 1-2'- sunny.  Air temp. 70 degrees F.
Public perception due to turbidity.  Winds light from SE- clear + sunny.  Air 75 degrees F.
Clear and sunny- winds are SE 15-20 mph- air temp is 75 degrees.
East-southeast winds 5 mph- sunny- air temp. 75 degrees F- minimal boat traffic.
Winds ESE5-10 mph- air temp. 85 degrees F- sunny- no boat traffic.
Winds are E-SE @ 10 mph- little boat activity- partly to mostly cloudy- air temp is 75 degrees.
Sunny- winds NW 5 mph- boating activity increasing turbidity- air temp. 85 degrees F.
E winds- 10 mph- sunny- heavy (2") rains- Friday p.m.  Increasing boating + jet ski.
SE winds 5 mph- partly cloudy- air temp. 80 degrees F- some boating activity.
Sunny- hot-  air temp. 80 degrees F - some boat activity.
Partly cloudy- winds are northwest. @ 5-10 mph- light boat activity- some jet skiers- air temp is 80 degrees.
Winds ESE @ 5 mph- sunny- air temp. 72 degrees F- heavy boating + jet skis.
Winds light + variable- sunny- air temp. 75 degrees F- jet skis in shallow water.
Winds are SW @ 5-10 mph- air temp is 73 degrees- mostly cloudy- rained earlier in the morning- no boat activity.  Water level: very low.
Mostly sunny- winds SE 10-15 mph- high winds + rain previous day- air temp. 50 degrees F.
Light (5-10) mph winds from west- mostly sunny- 60 degrees F.  Heavy rains 2 days prior.
Public perception due to turbidity. Sunny- east winds 10-15 mph- air temp. 50 degrees F- waves  less than 1'- jet ski active- some fishing.
Public perception due to turbidity. wind 12-15 mph from east. sunny- air temp. 62 degrees F- higher turbidity along west shore (wave induced).
Winds SE 5-10 mph- clear sky- air temp. 75 degrees F. Light boating activity- some rainfall on 7/2. Water has a different color than "normal".
Winds ESE 5-10 mph- light chop- mostly sunny- slight haze- moderate boating- multiple jet skies.  Water color is different this year.
Sunny- air temp. 75 degrees F- winds SE 15 mph- moderate boating- heavy rains several days ago-about 4".  Lake level: very high
Sunny- winds- 10 mph from SE.  Very little boat/jet ski activity.
Public perception due to turbidity. clear sky- 10-12 mph winds from south-southeast- light chop- minimal boat activity.
Public perception due to turbidity. clear sky- SE wind 5-10 mph- water temp. 80 degrees F- air temp. 80+ degrees F- moderate boat activity.
Heavy boating activity-many pwc. Clear sky- winds 10-15 mph from SE- air temp. 82 degrees F.
SE winds 15-18 mph- minimal boating- sunny.
Mostly cloudy- winds 5 mph from west-northeast- scattered showers- no boat activity- heavy rains 5-6 days previous.
Sunny- winds SE 15-20 mph-gusty- 60 degrees F- no boat activity.
Public perception due to turbidity- sunny- winds SW 15-20 mph- very gusty- no boat activity.
Mostly cloudy- calm- 46 degrees- no boat activity.
Partly sunny- east-northeast winds at 10-12 mph- moderate jet ski and light boat activity- the temperature is 60 degrees F.
Mostly sunny.  North winds at 5-10 mph.  No boat activity.  Good clarity.
Partly cloudy.  Winds 5-20 mph from north-northwest.  No boat activity. 60 degrees.
Sunny- winds north at 5 mph.  No boat activity.  55 degrees.
Mostly sunny- winds southeast at 20-25 mph.  No boat activity.  Air temperature is 78 degrees.  Some wind and wave induced turbidity.  Water level 1 inch over spillway.
Clear- sunny- NNW wind at 10-15 mph. Ice out today.
Sunny- SE wind 10-15 mph.  Jet ski active.
Sunny- SE wind 10-15 mph. 80 degrees- heavy rain previous.
Sunny- SE wind 5-10 mph. No boats.
Partly cloudy- NW wind 5-10 mph. 45 degrees.
SE 10 mph- mostly sunny. mod. Boats.
SE 5-10 mph- sunny (4.5 Ft secchi west shore).
SE 15 mph- sunny- major jet ski action.
N 5-10 mph- clear + sunny- no boats.
SE 15 mph- clear + sunny- mod. Boats.
SE 10-15 mph- clear + sunny- min. boats.
NE 5-10 mph- mostly sunny- jet skis.
SE 5-10 mph- clear + sunny- heavy rains prior.
W 5 mph- clear + sunny- heavy rains prior.
NW 5 mph- clear + sunny- min. boats.
ESE 5-10 mph- clear + sunny- min. boats.

SE 10-15 mph- mostly sunny- no boats.
NW 10 mph- clear + sunny- heavy rains prior.
SW 10 mph- Clear + Sunny-  mod. Boats
Light winds- Partly Sunny- heavy boat traffic
SE 15-20 mph- clear + sunny- Strong NW winds prior day
ESE 5-10 mph- clear + sunny- mod. Boat traffic
SE 10 mph- mostly sunny- HEAVY jet ski traffic on 7th + 8th
W 5-10 mph- clear + sunny- mod boat traffic
SE 10 mph- mostly sunny- mod boat traffic
Calm- partly cloudy- no boats- 1.5" rain prior day
ESE 5 mph- clear + sunny- min. boat traffic
SSE 10-15 mph- mostly sunny- mod. Boat traffic
E 15+ mph- rough lake- partly cloudy- min. boat traffic
ESE 5 mph- clear + sunny- min. boat traffic
SE-light- clear + sunny- mod. boat traffic
SE 15+ mph- mostly cloudy- min boat traffic- heavy rain prior day
SW 10-15 mph- clear + sunny- no boats
NW 10-15- clear + sunny- no boats- strong winds prior day
NW 10- clear + sunny- no boats- strong winds prior 2 days
SW 5-10 mph- partly cloudy- no boats
SE 5-10 mph- high clouds- some jet skis.
NW 10 mph- clear and sunny- heavy rains previous days.
light winds- clear and sunny- moderate boats.
SW 10-15 mph- clear and sunny- moderate boats.
SE 10 mph- clear and sunny- many jet skis.
SW 10-12 mph- clear and sunny- moderate jet boats/jet skis.
SW 10-15 mph- clean and sunny- many jet skis and boats.
SW 5-10 mph- clear and sunny (3.5 secchi offshore from beach).
SE 15-20 mph- partly sunny- moderate boat/jet ski traffic.
SE 5-10 mph- mostly sunny- some boats- many jet skis.
N 5-10 mph. Partly sunny- moderate boat/jet ski traffic.
N 10-15 mph- high thin clouds- no boats.
SE 10 mph- mostly cloudy- no boats.
NW 10+ mph- mostly cloudy- no boats.
SE wind- 10 mph- clear and sunny. Heavy winds/rains prior 2 days. Min. boats.
E 10-15 mph. High thin clouds. Min. boats.
SE winds 10-15 mph. Clear and sunny. Min. boats.
Light and variable. Partly cloudy. Min. boats.
NW 5 mph. Clear and sunny. Many boats/jet skis.
Light and variable. Clear and sunny. Many boats and jet skis.
Light and variable. Clear and sunny. Moderate boats and jet skis.
Light and variable. Clear and sunny. Moderate boats and jet skis.
NNE 15+ mph. Clear and sunny. Moderate boats and jet skis.
ESE  less than  5 mph. Partly cloudy. Min. boats/mod. jet skis.
Light/ Clear and sunny. Moderate boats and jet skis.
SE  less than  5 mph. Clear and sunny. Min. boats and jet skis. Strong winds prior.
7.2 meters deep- 10% cloud cover- 2 Custer color strip reading- slight algae
W  less than  5 mph. Clear and sunny. Moderate jet skis.
SW  less than  5 mph. Clear and sunny. Some jet skis and boats.
SE winds 10 mph. Clear and sunny. Min. boats and jet skis.
N winds light. Clear and sunny. No boats/jet skis.
Light. Clear and sunny. No boats/jet skis.
SW  less than  5 mph. Clear and sunny. No jet skis and boats.
Light and variable.  Partly sunny. No jet skis and boats.
SE 15 mph+- clear and sunny- very turbid.  No boats.
ESE 5-10 mph- mostly sunny- heavy rains and winds prior
SE 10 mph- mostly sunny- heavy rains prior- min. boats
SW 5-10 mph- sunny- min boats + jet skis.
ESE 5-10 mph- sunny- some jet skis
NNE 10-15 mph- mostly sunny- min boats + jet skis
SE 10 mph- clear + sunny- many boats and jet skis w/ neg. impact
N 10-15 mph- mostly sunny- some boats
SE 10-15 mph- clear + sunny- turbid look- no boats.
6+ jet skis- 2-3 speed boats.  Mostly cloudy.  South wind 10 mph.  Bottom temp. 70 F- bottom D.O. 6.2 mg/l.
Clear and sunny- WNW 10-15 mph.  6-8 jet skis and 3 water ski boats.
Strong (20 mph+) SE winds.  Few boats.  Mostly sunny.
Like NE clouds- clear and sunny- few boats
light NW clouds; calm- few boats- partly sunny
NNW 5mph- clear and sunny- few boats
WSW 5-10mph- clear and sunny- no boats
clear + sunny. no wind. few boats.
clear and sunny. SW winds 15 mph- 6+ boats 750 ml filtered for chlorophyl a
clear + sunny. light winds. 6+ boats 750 ml filtered for chlorophyl a
clear + sunny. 5mph winds from NW. very few boats
No cloud cover or precip- wind at 10mph.  Site depth of 7.0m with no apparent algae development.  Meter type: Quanta.  Depth of integrated water sample 0-2m.  800 mls filtered for chlorophyll.
No cloud cover- no precip- slight wind.  Site depth of 7.2m- slight algae development.  Meter type used: Quanta- depth of integrated water sample: 0-2m.  1000 ml filtered for chlorophyll.
sunny- winds SE at 10 mph. No boats
Partly suny- Light NNE winds. No boats. Significant runoff.
Suuny. winds wnw 15+- no boats. sunny. WNW winds 15+ mph. No boats. 0.25 inch rain prior evening.
Mostly cloudy- NW winds 10-15mph. No boats. Mostly cloudy- NW winds 10-15mph. No boats. 0.25 inch rain prior evening.
partly sunny. dead calm. 6+ boats. sunny. Dead calm. 6+ boats
SSW winds 10-12mph. overcast. Heavy rains prior days.
NNE winds less than 5mph. Rains several prior weeks. Sunny
SE 10 mph. Sunny. Heavy SSW winds pior day.
North winds less than 5mph- sunny- lake level high- algal blooms all spring
sunny- SW winds 5-10- no boats- very srong NW winds prior day.
mostly cloudy- calm- heavy rain prior days. no boats.
Light west winds- 1-3 boats on lake- clear + sunny.
Winds ESE @ 10 mph. Partly sunny- minimal boats.
SW winds less than 5 mph- overcast. 1-2 boats.
Clear + sunny. No boats. SSW winds 5-10 mph.
Finally- full ice-out. latest ice-out date in at least 20 years.
Sunny. Winds ESE 5 mph. No boats. lake level very high. Ice-out 4/24/13.
Water temp. at 25.22 C- air temp at 18.33C.0% cloud cover. Sample taken at 3ft. First lake sample from extra sampling program.
Air temp at 13.3C.- 100% cloud cover. Sample taken days after previous heavy rains.
mostly/partly cloudy- North winds at 5mph. Heavy rains last several days. sago pondweed growths across lake.
100% overcast. light drizzle. No boats. west winds about 10mph. Air. Temp 55.4 F.
Partly cloudy. South winds 5-8 mph. No boats. Air temp. 68.7 F. Strong S winds prior day.
Partly cloudy. SW winds 10-12 mph. 2 boats. strong SW winds over 2 prior days. 74.6 F air temp.
_Partly cloudy. Light/variable winds less than 2 mph. 2 boats.
I did duplicate and blanks on Clark Lake today (lab and equipment) 4 sets of samples (chl only with sample and duplicate)
Taken shortly after ice-out. Sunny. Light + variable winds. No boats. Strong winds on 4/11 + 4/12. Light rain on 4/13. Suspended algae bloom. Loon seen on lake.
full sun. ESE winds at 5mph. Rains + winds previous several days.
Overcast. NNE 10-15++. Rain overnight. bacterial mat on sand/rock around lake (brown). No DO readings below 3ft- as anchor line broke- and I was pushed off-station. :(
5-10mph winds from NNW. Sunny- no boats.
100 % sunny. NE 7-8mph. No boats. recently dry.
100% sunny. NW 5-10- no boats. 2.5" rain 4 days prior- brown bacteria covering in shallow water.
100% sunny. calm. 1-2 boats. 3/4" rain on 17th. Dense mats of red/brown coating - sample taken and sent to DNR.
Pat Canney and Mark Weise observed. mostly sunny. N winds @ 5-7 mph. 2-3 boats. little rain recently.
mostly cloudy- winds 5-10 ESE. 1-2 boats fishing. Relatively dry weather. Bob D. helped.
full sun. 1-2 boats. winds about 5mph from SSE. VERY heavy rains prior days.
air temp 70 f. SE 5 mph. 50% overcast. wet summer so far. little boating. carp die-off 1-2 weeks ago.
65 air temp. 75% overcast. High winds 2-3 days prior. No boating. carp die-off finally done.
95% clear. ENE wind at 5-10mph. No boats. 1.5 inch rain previous several days.
light overcast. mostly sunny. ESE at 10-15mph. No boats. dry period.
clear + sunny. wind NNW at 5mph. minimal boating. dry period continues. clear + sunny. NNW at 5 mph. minimal boating. dry period continues.
Sampled with Holly Stegeman from DNR. QA/QC effort. fully cloudy. N at 10mph. No boats. 1.5 inch rain pervious 2 days.
mostly cloudy- winds NE 15-20mph. No boats. Heavy rain- 1.2" prior night. wind too strong to anchor - held station with motor.
clear + sunny. No boats- SW winds at 10-15+mph. 0.5" inch rain prior night.
Partly cloudy- no boats. Winds N 10-12+mph. 4-6" rain prior week.
clear + sunny. virtually calm. No boats. (light SW wind developing). satellite flyover today.
Winds SSE 12-15 mph. mostly sunny - light haze. 6-7" rain a week ago.
Winds SSE 5-10 mph. no boats. Sunny. Sampler broke - samples only at 3ft depth.
Winds NNW at 5-10mph. several fishing boats. Mostly sunny. 0.7" rain prior day.
winds NW at less than 5mph. clear + sunny. - slightly hazy. 0.6" rain on Saturday.
